 * Immutable (persistent) vector with structural sharing.
 *
 * The implementation follows the classic 32‑ary tree design used by Clojure's
 * PersistentVector.  All mutating operations return a new vector while sharing
 * unchanged parts of the underlying tree.
 *
 * API:
 *   - static empty<T>(): PersistentVector<T>
 *   - get size(): number
 *   - get(i: number): T                // throws RangeError if out of bounds
 *   - push(value: T): PersistentVector<T>
